=== Bolton XI ===
On 20 May, Bolton announced their annual pre-season fixture against [[Chorley F.C.|Chorley]] in the Harold Taylor Memorial Trophy would take place on 26 July. This announcement was followed by a Bolton XI's finalised pre-season schedule with games against [[Bamber Bridge F.C.|Bamber Bridge]], [[Hyde F.C.|Hyde]], [[Melbourne Heart FC|Melbourne Heart]], [[A.F.C. Fylde|Fylde]] and [[Wrexham F.C.|Wrexham]] also taking place. After the announcement of the fixtures, Melbourne Heart were purchased by [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Melbourne Heart taken over by Manchester City-led consortium|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25854631|website=www.bbc.co.uk|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=17 June 2014}}</ref> and were rebranded as Melbourne City, while also signing [[Damien Duff]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Damien Duff makes Melbourne City move|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27776082|website=www.bbc.co.uk|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=17 June 2014}}</ref> and [[David Villa]].<ref>{{cite web|title=David Villa to play for Melbourne before New York MLS move|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27710040|website=www.bbc.co.uk|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation|accessdate=17 June 2014}}</ref>

[[Conor Wilkinson]] opened the scoring in the Bolton XI's first game against [[Bamber Bridge F.C.|Bamber Bridge]], with Stuart Vasey equalising for the hosts. The following game against [[Hyde F.C.]] was postponed due to bad weather. They then hosted [[Melbourne City FC|Melbourne City]], where, despite scoring an early goal through Conor Wilkinson, they lost 5-1, with Kisnorbo, Williams, Brown, Dugandzic and [[Aaron Mooy]], formerly of Wanderers, all scoring for the visitors. They then went to [[Chorley F.C.|Chorley]] where Wilkinson again scored the opening goal, but Chorley won the game with goals from Harry Winter and [[Tom Smyth]]. Danny Lloyd scored the only goal of Bolton XI's penultimate game of pre-season, as Bolton lost 1-0 to [[A.F.C. Fylde]], but in their final pre-season game, Bolton XI got their first win of pre-season as they beat [[Wrexham F.C.|Wrexham]] 1-0 courtesy of [[Chris Lester]]'s first half goal. During pre-season ex-[[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]] defender [[Liam Fontaine]] was on trial for the club,<ref>{{cite web|author1=Marc Iles|title=Wanderers to make a decision on ex-Bristol City defender Liam Fontaine on Monday|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/sport/11383432.Wanderers_to_make_a_decision_on_ex_Bristol_City_defender_Liam_Fontaine_on_Monday/?ref=rss|website=www.theboltonnews.co.uk|publisher=The Bolton News|accessdate=6 August 2014}}</ref> playing in matches against [[A.F.C. Fylde|Fylde]] and [[Wrexham F.C.|Wrexham]]. On 6 August it was revealed that Fontaine had discontinued training with the club at the start of that week, after plans for a behind-closed-doors friendly against [[Udinese Calcio|Udinese]] were shelved.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Marc Iles|title=Former Bristol City man Liam Fontaine leaves Bolton Wanderers after trial period|url=http://www.theboltonnews.co.uk/sport/wanderers/wanderersnews/11392366._/?ref=mac|website=www.theboltonnews.co.uk|publisher=The Bolton News|accessdate=7 August 2014}}</ref>

